The Professional Breakdown:
As asphalt shingles age, they lose the granules that protect your home from UV rays and water. In the insurance world, an old roof is a liability, not an asset.

If a massive storm rolls through the Triad and rips up your 20-year-old roof, you might expect a check for a brand-new one. STOP RIGHT THERE.

Depending on your policy, you might only get the Actual Cash Value (ACV). That means you get paid what your old, tired roof is worth todayâ€”not what it costs to buy a new one in 2024. That's the difference between a full payout and a check that barely covers the dumpster rental.
